.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_Slider
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: Attaching the script to a game object will allow the user to interact with it as if it were a horizontal or vertical slider. The direction can be freely set and auto-detection is supported.
.NET Framework 3.5.remarks: The script will instantiate the required Rigidbody and Interactable components automatically in case they do not exist yet.
.NET Framework 3.5.example: VRTK/Examples/025_Controls_Overview has a selection of sliders at various angles with different step values to demonstrate their usage.
